==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: brierwood
<hw>bri"er*wood`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>wood from the hard
woody root of the briar <spn>Erica arborea</spn>; it is used to make
tobacco pipes. See also 2nd <er>brier</er> and <cref>brier
root</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> briarwood.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

